{
  "stem": "16214.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So-- however, my mother, not hearing anything from my father and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] worrying about what's-- what's happening, and trying to rescue herself and rescue me-- and especially being told so many times by elder people that she's too young to die-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] she decided that she would do that.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, from what I understand, they had the theater group, which was active in Warsaw Ghetto-- helped my mother, because they helped her financially to escape.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it's almost miraculous to see how she got out of there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But sometimes in August, I-- August, I believe, of 1942, she just held me on her arms and she just walked out with me while people were going to work.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So she sort of smuggled herself out with them, with a whole group of people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And from what I understand, she could have sworn that some of the-- the German must have seen her and-- who was watching the people.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But somehow, he would let her go.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And maybe because she was very pretty, very blonde-- long blonde hair, beautiful lady.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he just allowed her to escape.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But who knows, you know?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And from what I know, she [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] took a horse-drawn carriage to a station, where she could from there go [? to Goleniow. ?] [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] She arrived at the station.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she was told that this-- the train just left.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was very upset because it meant she had to stay for another-- the entire day, till evening-- and worrying that perhaps someone may recognize her or someone may say something, because after all, she was with me.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Didn't carry really any-- anything.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She looked sort of-- she may have looked suspicious.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
